# GitHub CODEOWNERS for mattsears18/shipyard
#
# This file requires named reviewers to approve PRs that touch listed paths
# when "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in the branch protection
# rule for `main`. Branch protection is configured manually in the repo
# Settings UI; this file alone does not enforce review — it only declares
# WHO must review WHAT once the branch-protection toggle is on.
#
# Order matters: GitHub uses the LAST matching pattern, so put more-specific
# rules below less-specific ones.

# --- Security boundary: trusted-author allowlist -----------------------------
#
# `.shipyard/trusted-authors.txt` is the single security gate that decides
# which issue authors `/shipyard:do-work` will dispatch autonomous workers
# against (see plugins/shipyard/commands/do-work.md step 1.7). Anyone with
# `write` access could otherwise extend the allowlist via a single PR with
# no maintainer in the loop, which is a privilege-escalation surface
# (see issue #139). Require the repo owner to review changes to this file.
.shipyard/trusted-authors.txt @mattsears18
